package templates

templ PrivacyPage() {
    @Layout("privacy policy") {
        <article>
            <hgroup>
                <h1>privacy policy</h1>
                <p>last updated: july 10, 2026</p>
            </hgroup>

            <section>
                <h2>what runway is</h2>
                <p>
                runway is a personal finance tool that connects to your bank accounts to
                help you track spending. it operates as a
                <a href="https://telegram.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="sc">telegram</span></a>
                bot and is available on an invite-only basis.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>data we collect</h2>
                <p>when you use runway, we collect and store the following information:</p>
                <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong><span class="sc">telegram</span> account identifiers</strong>:
                    your <span class="sc">telegram</span> user id, used to associate your
                    account with the bot.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>financial account metadata</strong>: the name and type of
                    accounts you connect (e.g. "checking," "credit card"), as provided by
                    your financial institution through
                    <a href="https://plaid.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="sc">plaid</span></a>.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>transaction data</strong>: transaction descriptions, amounts,
                    dates, and categories, synced from your connected accounts through
                    <span class="sc">plaid</span>'s transaction sync api.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong><span class="sc">plaid</span> access tokens</strong>:
                    credentials that allow runway to retrieve your financial data on an
                    ongoing basis. these are stored in encrypted form
                    (see <a href="#security">security</a> below).
                </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                runway does <strong>not</strong> collect or store your bank login
                credentials. authentication with your financial institution is handled
                entirely by <span class="sc">plaid</span>'s secure link flow.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>how we use your data</h2>
                <p>your data is used to:</p>
                <ul>
                <li>display your recent transactions and account balances.</li>
                <li>calculate daily and periodic spending summaries.</li>
                <li>
                    generate optional ai-powered spending commentary via a third-party
                    language model provider
                    (<a href="https://openrouter.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="sc">openrouter</span></a>).
                    when this feature is used, summarized or aggregated spending data may be
                    sent to the language model. raw transaction details and account
                    credentials are never sent.
                </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>third-party services</h2>
                <p>runway uses the following third-party services to function:</p>
                <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong><a href="https://plaid.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="sc">plaid</span></a></strong>:
                    used to securely connect to your financial institution and retrieve
                    account and transaction data. when you connect an account, your data is
                    transmitted through <span class="sc">plaid</span>'s systems.
                    <span class="sc">plaid</span>'s handling of your data is governed by the
                    <a href="https://plaid.com/legal/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="sc">plaid</span> privacy policy</a>.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong><a href="https://telegram.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="sc">telegram</span></a></strong>:
                    the messaging platform through which you interact with runway. messages
                    you send to the bot pass through <span class="sc">telegram</span>'s
                    infrastructure.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong><a href="https://openrouter.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="sc">openrouter</span></a></strong>:
                    a language model api provider, used only when ai-generated spending
                    commentary is requested. only aggregated spending summaries are sent; no
                    raw financial data or credentials are transmitted.
                </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                runway does not sell, rent, or share your financial data with any other
                third parties.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section id="security">
                <h2>security</h2>
                <p>
                runway takes reasonable measures to protect your data.
                <span class="sc">plaid</span> access tokens are encrypted using
                industry-standard aes encryption both at rest and in memory while the
                application is running. all other stored data, including
                <span class="sc">telegram</span> account identifiers, financial account
                metadata, and transaction history, is encrypted at rest. the application
                database is hosted on private infrastructure and is not publicly
                accessible.
                </p>
                <p>
                while we take care to protect your information, no system is perfectly
                secure. runway is a small, personally operated project, not a commercial
                financial institution.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>data retention and deletion</h2>
                <p>
                your data is retained for as long as your account is active. you may
                delete your data at any time by using the <code>/unregister</code>
                command in the <span class="sc">telegram</span> bot. this will delete
                your stored transactions, revoke your <span class="sc">plaid</span>
                access tokens, and remove your user record from the database.
                </p>
                <p>
                deletion is permanent. data that has already been transmitted to
                third-party services (<span class="sc">plaid</span>,
                <span class="sc">telegram</span>,
                <span class="sc">openrouter</span>) is subject to those services' own
                retention policies.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>changes to this policy</h2>
                <p>
                this policy may be updated from time to time. material changes will be
                communicated through the <span class="sc">telegram</span> bot. continued
                use of runway after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>contact</h2>
                <p>{ "if " }you have questions about this policy or want to request data deletion,
                contact the operator at:
                <a href="mailto:hayden@inetd.cafe">hayden@inetd.cafe</a>
                </p>
            </section>
            </article>
    }
}